---
// Root 404 page → emitted by Astro as dist/404.html.
//
// GitHub Pages serves THIS file (the site-wide custom 404) for ANY unmatched
// path on the custom domain — including deep-links under a published Slidev
// deck, e.g. /slides/<slug>/10 or /slides/<slug>/presenter/3.
//
// WHY THIS IS NEEDED (verified 2026-06, Slidev 52.x):
//   The decks live at /slides/<slug>/ (copied by deploy.yml into dist/slides/).
//   Slidev v52 uses PATH-based slide routing: slide N is the URL
//   /slides/<slug>/N, and the SPA router reads the slide number from the URL
//   PATH AT BOOT. The deck root /slides/<slug>/ is a real file (HTTP 200), but
//   /slides/<slug>/10 is NOT a file on disk → GitHub Pages returns its built-in
//   "Page not found" page. The deck's own dist/slides/<slug>/404.html is never
//   served for that path (Pages does not do per-directory 404 fallback on this
//   custom-domain topology), and the deck's _redirects file is Netlify-only —
//   GitHub Pages ignores it.
//
// THE FIX (empirically validated against the live deck with Playwright):
//   For a /slides/<slug>/<rest> miss, fetch the deck's index.html shell and swap
//   it into THIS document WITHOUT changing location. Because the URL stays at
//   /slides/<slug>/10, Slidev's path router boots straight onto slide 10.
//   - Tried & rejected: location.replace('/slides/<slug>/10') → 404 loop (the
//     path is still not a file).  ?p=/N and #N → Slidev v52 normalises to /1
//     (lands on slide 1, not N).  Document-injection is the only form that lands
//     on the correct slide AND keeps the clean /N URL.
//
// Any non-/slides/ miss just goes home (the site is bilingual and the root
// index.astro re-routes to the user's locale).
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex" />
    <title>Redirecting…</title>
    <script is:inline>
      (function () {
        var path = window.location.pathname;
        // Deep-link under a Slidev deck: /slides/<slug>/<rest>
        // (<rest> = slide number, or presenter/N, overview, etc.)
        var m = path.match(/^\/slides\/([^/]+)\/(.+)$/);
        if (m) {
          var slug = m[1];
          // Boot the deck SPA in place. We keep `location` exactly as requested
          // (/slides/<slug>/<rest>) so Slidev's path router lands on the right
          // slide; we only swap in the deck's HTML shell so its bundle loads.
          fetch('/slides/' + slug + '/index.html', { credentials: 'same-origin' })
            .then(function (r) {
              if (!r.ok) throw new Error('deck shell ' + r.status);
              return r.text();
            })
            .then(function (html) {
              document.open();
              document.write(html);
              document.close();
            })
            .catch(function () {
              // Deck shell unreachable (bad slug / not deployed) → home.
              window.location.replace('/');
            });
          return;
        }
        // Not a deck deep-link → send home (root re-routes to locale).
        window.location.replace('/');
      })();
    </script>
    <noscript>
      <meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0;url=/" />
    </noscript>
  </head>
  <body style="background:#0F172A;color:#94A3B8;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;min-height:100vh;font-family:system-ui;margin:0;">
    <p>Page not found — <a href="/" style="color:#14B8A6;">go home</a>.</p>
  </body>
</html>
